1 2. Have on file with the director of teacher education at an
2 Oklahoma institution of higher education a plan for meeting standard
3 certification requirements within three (3) years; and
4 3. Participate in an induction program as required in Section
5 6-195 of this title and have the same duties and responsibilities as
6 other inductees.
7 D. The State Board of Education may grant an exception to the
8 requirements for certification and, upon demonstration by an
9 individual of specific competency in the subject area of
10 specialization, may grant a certificate to the individual. The
11 State Board may establish other requirements necessary to grant
12 exceptions.
13 E. The State Board of Education, in consultation with the
14 Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability, may grant an
15 exception to the requirement to complete a subject area examination
16 for initial certification in a field which does not require an
17 advanced degree pursuant to this section if the candidate has an
18 advanced degree in a subject that is substantially comparable to the
19 content assessed on a subject area examination. The degree shall be
20 from an institution accredited by a national or regional accrediting
21 agency which is recognized by the Secretary of the U.S. Department
22 of Education. The Commission shall provide the Board with the
23 necessary information to determine comparability.
24
Req. No. 12980 Page 5

1 F. Student teaching and a prestudent teaching field experience
2 shall not be required of alternative placement program participants
3 for standard certification.
4 G. 1. The State Board of Education and the State Board of
5 Career and Technology Education shall promulgate rules authorizing
6 adjunct teachers who shall be persons with distinguished
7 qualifications in their field. Adjunct teachers shall not be
8 required to meet standard certification. A person employed as an
9 adjunct teacher pursuant to this subsection who does not hold a
10 valid certificate to teach shall not be considered a teacher as
11 defined by Section 1-116 of this title.
12 2. The State Department of Education shall work with the
13 Department of Career and Technology Education as necessary to
14 implement the rules promulgated by the State Board of Career and
15 Technology Education as authorized by paragraph 1 of this subsection
16 including, but not limiting to, issuing any necessary credentials.
17 H. Each teacher education institution shall provide the
18 Oklahoma Commission for Teacher Preparation an annual report of
19 information as specified by the Commission regarding participation
20 in the alternative placement programs offered by the institution.
21 I. The Oklahoma Commission for Teacher Preparation shall not
22 accredit, renew the accreditation of, or otherwise approve any
23 teacher education program of any institution of higher education in
24 this state that has not implemented alternative placement programs
Req. No. 12980 Page 6

1 in a t least four areas of specialization including mathematics,
2 science and a foreign language. Each institution shall allow
3 individuals who meet the criteria of subsections A and C of this
4 section to be:
5 1. Admitted to an alternative placement program without further
6 qualification; and
7 2. Offered the opportunity to complete the requirements for
8 standard certification set forth in subsection A of this section
9 during the summer preceding and the summer following the first year
10 of teaching with an alternative placement teaching certificate. Any
11 person seeking standard certification through an alternative
12 placement program shall be permitted to take necessary courses
13 during regular semesters if offered.
14 J. The criteria specified in subsection I of this section can
15 be met through a cooperative arrangement entered into by two or more
16 institutions of higher education.
17 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
18 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
19 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
20 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
21 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
